<p>Although I use Markdown, I prefer <code>&lt;img&gt;</code> tags to the <code>!</code> syntax. <a href="#fnref:md" rev="footnote">↩</a></p>
</li>
<li id="fn:safari">
<p>Safari, unfortunately, has the worst MathML renderer of the browsers I’ve tested. What it shows is certainly readable, but the baseline is inconsistent, making the equations look a bit tipsy. <a href="#fnref:safari" rev="footnote">↩</a></p>
</li>
</ol>
